1. Data Overview

This report analyzes the monthly factor returns for the Thai market. We replicated these factors in Thai data following Charoenwong, Nettayanun, and Saengchote (2021). The data includes:

  • Fama-French 6 Factors (FF6) (Fama & French, 2015): Market (mkt), Size (smb), Value (hml), Profitability (rmw), Investment (cma), and Momentum (umd).
  • q-factors (Hou, Xue, & Zhang, 2015): Market Equity (me), Investment-to-Assets (ia), Return on Equity (roe).
  • Behavioral & Other Factors:
    • Short-term Reversal (Momentum) (mom1) (Jegadeesh & Titman, 1995).
    • Betting Against Beta (beta) (Frazzini & Pedersen, 2014).
    • Volatility (vol, ivol) (Ang, Hodrick, Xing, & Zhang, 2006).
    • Illiquidity (illiq) (Amihud, 2002).
    • Behavioral Factors (Daniel, Hirshleifer, & Sun, 2020): Post-Earnings Announcement Drift (pead), Financing (fin).
